// Different between JS Object and JSON(Javascript Object Notetion)



// Syntac of JS Object :-

// const ans{
//     name : 'sumant',
//     age :32,
//     address : "palamu"
// }
// 2> javascript me undefined hota hai
// 3> javascript me last value ke baad comma(,) allow hai 
// 4> javascript me function likh sakte hai 
// 4> javascript key and value ke fkormate me hota hai
// 5> javascript Universal language nahi hai ise sirf JS hi samjhta hai




// Syntac of JSON :-

// const ans{
//     "name" : 'sumant',
//     "age" :32,
//     "address" : "palamu"
// }
// 2> JSON me undefined nahi hota hai
// 3> JSON me last value ke baad comma(,) allow nahi hota hai 
// 4> JSON me function likh nahi sakte hai
// 5> JSON string ke formate me hota hai 
// 6> JSON Universal language ha iss sab language samjhte hai (C,C++,JAVA,JSON,Python,etc)